because LED lights last up to five times longer than halogen bulbs. However, halogens are significantly lower in price, so it will initially save you money at the register. LED lights also use less energy and shine much brighter than halogens. The benefits of LED now greatly reign over the benefits of halogens, except when it comes to price. <br /><br /><br /><h4>Seat Kits</h4>There are many different kinds of seat kits to choose from, some of the steel and some of the aluminum varieties. Steel is the more durable of the two, although it is heavier which could have an effect on your top speed. One of the drawbacks with steel is that it is prone to rust whereas aluminum seats are free of any rust problems. Those who live in areas by the beach, where there is a lot of salt in the air, may want to go with the aluminum variety.<br /><br /><br /><h4>OEM or Custom-made</h4>When buying most types of <a href="http://carolinagolfcars.com/parts-accessories/" target="_blank">golf cart accessories</a>, it is important to be familiar with the term OEM which stands for Original Equipment Manufacturer. This refers to parts and accessories made by the original cart manufacturer. There is also the option of choosing from custom accessories, which are made to your specific liking. This option is generally the more expensive of the two. Many times, options are greater in the custom made variety, but be prepared to pay.<br /><br /><br /><div><h4>Speakers</h4>Speakers can be just as important in a golf cart as they are in a car. And it is important to remember that quality matters when it comes to speakers. Quality extends beyond sound as some speakers are equipped with hardware that will not rust. Some speakers also have components that are sealed. This will protect the speakers from the unforgiving elements of nature. Speakers with a little flexibility also impact exactly where they can be mounted.<br /><br /><br />Parts and accessories from the leading manufacturers are widely available at Carolina Golf Cars, which is also a top choice for golf carts rentals,<a href="http://carolinagolfcars.com/cart-sales/" target="_blank"> new/used golf carts for sale</a> and much more. Get expert advice and golf cart customization services from the Carolina?s premier golf car dealership, Carolina Golf Cars. </div>";s:9:"link_edit";s:82:"http://www.blogger.com/feeds/6350081566167736342/posts/default/7066093123299549634";s:9:"link_self";s:82:"http://www.blogger.com/feeds/6350081566167736342/posts/default/7066093123299549634";s:4:"link";s:83:"http://carolinagolfcars.blogspot.com/2016/04/how-to-accessorize-your-golf-cart.html";s:11:"author_name";s:12:"Ricky Haidar";s:10:"author_uri";s:45:"https://plus.google.com/100378077812297189188";s:12:"author_email";s:19:"noreply@blogger.com";}i:22;a:11:{s:2:"id";s:70:"tag:blogger.com,1999:blog-6350081566167736342.post-8091247026084670434";s:9:"published";s:29:"2016-03-14T13:10:00.000-04:00";s:7:"updated";s:29:"2017-03-29T14:47:30.960-04:00";s:5:"title";s:50:" The Process of Making Your Golf Cart Street Legal";s:12:"atom_content";s:3522:"<span style="font-family: inherit;">Being able to drive your golf cart on the street offers convenience and excitement. However, it does not come without following a certain protocol. Here is a look at all of the areas that need to be addressed before your golf cart can be considered legal to drive in the street.&nbsp;</span><br /><span style="font-family: inherit;"><br /></span><h4><span style="font-family: inherit;">Paperwork</span></h4><span style="font-family: inherit;">When you <a href="http://carolinagolfcars.com/cart-sales/" target="_blank">buy a golf cart</a> you will need the proper documentation, which includes all the pertinent information you will need to make it legal. There will be an ID number issued, which is similar to a VIN number on a motor vehicle. There will also be paperwork provided by the golf cart manufacturer which states its speeds. That is a requirement to classify it as a low-speed vehicle since that is how it will be registered.&nbsp;</span><br /><span style="font-family: inherit;"><br /></span><h4><span style="font-family: inherit;">Safety Functions</span></h4><span style="font-family: inherit;">Headlights are required as they provide safety at night, dusk, damn, and during times of bad weather. Taillights are also a must as they alert any vehicles travelling behind the golf cart of its presence on the road. Turn signals are another requirement, just as they would be in any other kind of motor vehicle. Seat belts are one more safety function that is mandatory. There must be enough seat belts for each passenger, which generally tops off at four.&nbsp;</span><br /><span style="font-family: inherit;"><br /></span><h4><span style="font-family: inherit;">Visibility&nbsp;</span></h4><span style="font-family: inherit;">In order to be considered <a href="http://carolinagolfcars.com/cart-sales/street-legal-lsvs/" target="_blank">street legal, golf carts</a> have to be equipped with side view and rear view mirrors. There also has to be a windshield installed, one that is durable enough to maintain the safety of the passengers while also providing clear visibility for the driver.&nbsp;</span><br /><br /><h4><span style="font-family: inherit;">Brakes</span></h4><span style="font-family: inherit;">Front and rear brakes are required and they must also be independent brakes. This will ensure that the golf cart will be able to stop on its own, without the assistance of another vehicle or object. A parking brake is also required to ensure safety when the vehicle is immobile.&nbsp;</span><br /><span style="font-family: inherit;"><br /></span><h4><span style="font-family: inherit;">Road Rules</span></h4><span style="font-family: inherit;">Certain municipalities and communities have restrictions on street legal golf carts. Check with your local branch and learn about any qualifications or restrictions that may apply. Also remember that you are expected to adhere to the rules of the road and can be ticketed by police just as you would be when driving a car.</span><br /><span style="font-family: inherit;"><br /></span><span style="font-family: inherit;">Carolina Golf Cars offers a large selection of street legal golf carts for sale. And if you need some kind of accessories to add to your used golf cart, our vast supply of inventory has you covered. For the very best in golf cart sales and golf cart repair, visit the professionals at <a href="http://carolinagolfcars.com/" target="_blank">Carolina Golf Cars North Carolina</a>.&nbsp;</span><br /><br />";s:9:"link_edit";s:82:"http://www.blogger.com/feeds/6350081566167736342/posts/default/8091247026084670434";s:9:"link_self";s:82:"http://www.blogger.com/feeds/6350081566167736342/posts/default/8091247026084670434";s:4:"link";s:86:"http://carolinagolfcars.blogspot.com/2016/03/the-process-of-making-your-golf-cart.html";s:11:"author_name";s:12:"Ricky Haidar";s:10:"author_uri";s:45:"https://plus.google.com/100378077812297189188";s:12:"author_email";s:19:"noreply@blogger.com";}i:23;a:11:{s:2:"id";s:70:"tag:blogger.com,1999:blog-6350081566167736342.post-6918439230703987805";s:9:"published";s:29:"2016-03-02T13:12:00.002-05:00";s:7:"updated";s:29:"2017-03-29T14:47:30.921-04:00";s:5:"title";s:30:"Ways to Upgrade Your Golf Cart";s:12:"atom_content";s:3390:"Make your golf cart your very own is all part of the fun. With some upgrades you can better tailor your cart to your needs and desires, whether they be functional or aesthetic. Not all golf cart upgrades require major engine or body work and not all upgrades have to cost a fortune. Here is a look at some affordable upgrades that can change the entire look of your golf cart from <a href="http://carolinagolfcars.com/" target="_blank">Carolina Golf Cars of Charlotte</a>.<br /><br /><br /><h4>Lift Kits</h4>Having a lift kit added to your golf cart is an easy way to make a bold statement. By raising the body of the golf cart further from the ground you will gain more ground clearance. This means there is less risk of bottoming out and potential damaging your carts, especially when driving off-road or on uneven terrain. Lift kits are also beneficial to those operating a street legal golf cart, A.K.A low speed vehicle. The added height a lift kit creates will make the golf cart more visible to regular motor vehicles, certainly those with their own lift kits.<br /><br /><br /><h4><a href="https://2.bp.blogspot.com/-me5EQZWqAbg/Vtcsmeo7J-I/AAAAAAAABcI/thwL17d0_Mw/s1600/bigstock-Golf-Car-2082643.jpg" imageanchor="1" style="clear: right; float: right; margin-bottom: 1em; margin-left: 1em;"><img border="0" height="213" src="https://2.bp.blogspot.com/-me5EQZWqAbg/Vtcsmeo7J-I/AAAAAAAABcI/thwL17d0_Mw/s320/bigstock-Golf-Car-2082643.jpg" width="320" /></a>Hubcaps and Rims</h4>The selection of hub caps and rims for golf carts is just as extensive as it is for cars. Turbine hubcaps or chromed rims are just a couple of varieties that can really make your golf cart stand out from the rest of the pack. <a href="http://carolinagolfcars.com/parts-accessories/" target="_blank">http://carolinagolfcars.com/parts-accessories/</a> has a variety of hubcaps, rims, and tires to select from.<br /><br /><br /><h4>Seat Cushions </h4>Deluxe seat cushions can provide your golf cart with a completely different look. These are available in a wide array of colors. Brightening up the inside if your golf cart is a cheaper alternative to getting a custom paint job. But combining colored seat cushions with a custom paint job will really enhance the look of your cart. <br /><br /><br /><h4>Steering Wheel</h4>There are lots of different steering wheels you can incorporate to your golf cart. A wood-grain steering wheel can provide a more elegant look while camouflage steering wheels go great with off-road custom golf carts used for hunting. Steering wheel covers are also available in wide varieties. <br /><br /><br /><h4>Custom Paint</h4>Why settled for any ordinary color golf cart when your cart can truly stand out? Custom paint jobs are pretty much unlimited. If you can think it, someone can paint it. This is not only limited to color, but it extends to designs as well. If you want a golf cart with flames on the side, there is no reason you cannot have it.<br /><br /><br />Carolina Golf Cars has the capability to provide you with the golf cart of your dreams. Whether you are looking for a used golf cart, <a href="http://carolinagolfcars.com/cart-sales/new-golf-carts/" target="_blank">street legal golf carts or Yamaha golf carts</a>, there is something for everyone in our showroom. Carolina Golf Cars also offers golf car repair and accessories from all the industry leaders.";s:9:"link_edit";s:82:"http://www.blogger.com/feeds/6350081566167736342/posts/default/6918439230703987805";s:9:"link_self";s:82:"http://www.blogger.com/feeds/6350081566167736342/posts/default/6918439230703987805";s:4:"link";s:80:"http://carolinagolfcars.blogspot.com/2016/03/ways-to-upgrade-your-golf-cart.html";s:11:"author_name";s:12:"Ricky Haidar";s:10:"author_uri";s:45:"https://plus.google.com/100378077812297189188";s:12:"author_email";s:19:"noreply@blogger.com";}i:24;a:11:{s:2:"id";s:70:"tag:blogger.com,1999:blog-6350081566167736342.post-8039908684926627554";s:9:"published";s:29:"2015-10-26T18:20:00.000-04:00";s:7:"updated";s:29:"2017-03-29T14:47:30.957-04:00";s:5:"title";s:66:"Carolina Golf Cars adds Taylor-Dunn to its Commercial Product Line";s:12:"atom_content";s:3537:"Carolina Golf Cars has always been revered for carrying the top brands, parts and accessories that go along with golf cart sales. Now, there is another industry leader whose products can be purchased at Carolina Golf Cars. Taylor-Dunn has flourished for more than 60 years and Carolina Golf Cars is now an authorized dealer of <a href="http://carolinagolfcars.com/cart-sales/multi-passenger-utility-vehicles/taylor-dunn/" target="_blank">Taylor-Dun